title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1985-04-06
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, They Love Each Other, Minglewood Blues, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Mama Tried, Big River, Big Railroad Blues, Looks Like Rain-> Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> The Other One-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text:
Drugs make Music Sound Better  I had a truly wonderful out of body experience at this show and this recording is clean. 
However, Jerry’s voice is completely SHOT. 
I strongly recommend the next 2 Spectrum shows of this 3 night run as they went out of their way to Blow Minds. “Hiya Hiya Hiya Kids, Can you Hear Me?!? (Phil).
